that the missing ammunition cannot be found on any list. 
  According to an official statement by Matvey Burlakov, the 
commander in chief of the Russian forces in eastern Germany, the 
ammunition was used up at training sites, said Bundeswehr 
Lieutenant Commander Klaus Heermeier. However, he thinks that 
this is completely unlikely. [passage omitted] 

