<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Majority Support Air Strikes in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1502101194 Paris LE POINT in French 12 Feb 94 p 29 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1502101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE POINT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "IPSOS-LE POINT Opinion Poll"] </F>
  [Text] A national sample of 800 people representing the 
French population 18 and older were polled by telephone on 8 and 
9 February 1994 using the representative quotas method. 
Following are the results: 
<H3>  Should French UN troops stay in Bosnia or should they be 
pulled out? </H3>
  They should stay: 58 percent 
  They should be pulled out: 28 percent 
  Don't know: 14 percent 
<H5>  Should NATO bomb Serbian artillery positions around Sarajevo? </H5>
  Yes: 54 percent 
  No: 29 percent 
  Don't know: 17 percent 
<H5>  Should French troops take part in the air strikes if NATO </H5>

decides to bomb Serbian artillery positions around Sarajevo? 
  Yes: 70 percent 
  No: 21 percent 
  Don't know: 9 percent 
<H3>  Should the French authorities accept risking French military 
losses in the fighting taking place in the former Yugoslavia? </H3>
  Yes: 55 percent 
  No: 35 percent 
  Don't know: 10 percent 

</TEXT>

