<H3> <TI>   EC Cuts in Aid to Italian Agriculture Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0802111594 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1933 GMT 7 
Feb 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0802111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Cuts in Aid to Agriculture"] </F>
  [Text] Rome, 7 Feb (ANSA) -- Once again the lack of 
controls has compromised European Community aid to Italy which 
will receive 586.1 billion lire less from FEOGA, the fund that 
finances the common agricultural policy. 
  The Agricultural Ministry today noted that the cut came in 
line with the November 1993 decision on the part of the European 
Commission to liquidate the 1990 acccounts and stressed that 
every year Italy suffers the biggest reductions in FEOGA funds 
because of failure to respect Community controls and the terms 
within which payments must be made. 

</TEXT>

