<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Italy &amp; Vatican City </F>
<H3> <TI>   Democratic Alliance Joins Progressive Front </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1002134494 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1250 GMT 10 
Feb 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1002134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Democratic Alliance Returns to </F>
Progressive Front"] 
  [Text] Rome, 10 Feb (ANSA) -- The Democratic Alliance 
grouping will join the Progressives, the left-wing cartel to 
present joint candidates for the March 27 general elections, 
Democratic Alliance leader Ferdinando Adornato said Thursday [10 
February]. 
  Democratic Alliance chiefs were amongst those of eight 
parties which recently announced the formation of the 
Progressive cartel, but the loose grouping of left-wing 
intellectuals withdrew its support shortly after, in protest 
over positions struck by the Progressives. 
  Today's decision to return to the fold came after assurances 
from the other parties in the cartel, which is dominated by the 
Left Democrat Party, that the Progressives would continue with 
the economic recovery programme set in motion by current Premier 
Carlo Azeglio Ciampi. 
  Also important were guarantees from the Left Democrats on 
elements in the cartel's programme, and on candidate selection. 

</TEXT>

