<H3> <TI>   PDS Funding, Officials Under Investigation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1602130594 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1041 GMT 16 
Feb 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1602130594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "D'Alema of PDS Placed Under </F>
Investigation"] 
  [Text] Rome, 16 Feb (ANSA) -- Massimo D'Alema, the House 
whip for the Democratic Party of the Left (PDS) and considered 
the party's Number Two, has been placed under investigation 
along with eight others in connection with the investigation 
into illicit party funding, judicial sources said here today. 
  D'Alema this morning made a spontaneous appearance, 
accompanied by his attorney Guido Calvi, before Public 
Prosecutor Vittorio Mele, to give his version of the accusations 
made by former Socialist Partly leader and ex-Premier Bettino 
Craxi on alleged under-the-table contributions to the ex-Italian 
Communist Party (PCI), now the PDS. 
  Craxi recently presented a dossier to the justice department 
formally presenting his claims, already voiced on the floor of 
parliament, which must now be investigated to ascertain whether 
they are true or whether he should be indicted for slander. 
  The others Craxi claims were aware of the illicit 
contributions included PDS secretary Achille Occhetto and PDS 
administrative secretary Marcello Stefanini. 
  According to Craxi, the PCI and PDS received kickbacks for 
the so-called "Red Cooperatives" after they were awarded public 
contracts. 

</TEXT>

