<H3> <TI>   Russian Envoy Repeats Warning on NATO Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1702102494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0942 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1702102494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Saarbruecken (DDP/ADN) -- The Russian ambassador to 
Germany has again warned NATO of the consequences of air strikes 
in Bosnia. The use of force will "not solve any problems but 
will produce bigger ones," Ambassador [Vladimir] Terechov said 
on Saarlaendischer Radio today. Discussion in the West has 
concentrated "much too heavily" on the use of military means, 
the diplomat said. There was no better way to peace than 
through negotiations. 
  Terechov said the Russian Government is optimistic that a 
demilitarization of Sarajevo could be achieved "very soon" with 
"the good will" of the conflicting parties. His country is in 
constant touch with Serbia, Bosnia, and Croatia. "I believe 
Russia is doing good work," the ambassador stressed. 

</TEXT>

