<H3> <TI>   Three New Radio Stations To Broadcast in Berlin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1502214694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1747 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1502214694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (ADN-BLN) [Berlin regional office] -- The 
Media Council today issued three more FM frequencies in Berlin 
and Brandenburg. The stations in question are Radio Concept, 
Radio 50 Plus, and Sender Freies Berlin (SFB), which intends to 
broadcast a schedule for foreign minorities living in Berlin. 
  Radio Concept was allocated the frequency 98.2 MHz, which is 
at present being used by Deutschlandradio Cologne. The Media 
Council issued the station's organizers with the broadcasting 
permit for a "speech-oriented station with a cultural focus." 
The station Radio 50 plus, which is aimed largely at older 
listeners, will be available on 105.5 MHz. SFB was granted the 
frequency 106.8 MHz for its new station. 

</TEXT>

