<F P=100> BENELUX </F>
<F P=101> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnia's Karadzic: Air Strikes `Moral Disaster' for NATO </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1702120694 Brussels RTBF-1 Television Network in French 
1830 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BR1702120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels RTBF-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic by </F>
"special" correspondent Philippe Lamair; place and date not 
given; Karadzic speaks in English with superimposed French 
translation -- recorded] 
  [Text] For the first time in several days, a civilian in 
Sarajevo was killed by a sniper today. There were no other 
infringements of the cease-fire, however. Neither was there any 
sign from the Serbs, who are maintaining their position, 
although NATO has made it clear that the ultimatum would not be 
extended beyond the Sunday [20 February] midnight deadline. Our 
special correspondent in former Yugoslavia, Philippe Lamair, met 
with Radovan Karadzic, leader of the Bosnian Serbs. 
  [Lamair] [Question not heard] 
  [Karadzic] If all that NATO is trying to do is make us 
withdraw our artillery without also controlling the Muslim 
infantry, then there will be a strategic imbalance and the war 
will continue. I believe the threats should stop and diplomacy 
should go forth. If the international community treats both 
sides on equal footing, then there will be a peace accord. If 
the sanctions against Serbia are lifted, for example, then the 
Muslims will sign a peace [agreement], not before. 
  [Lamair] [Question not heard] 
  [Karadzic] I believe that the United States wants to flex 
its 
muscles, humiliate Russia, and scare other countries. NATO is 
just like a young man who has lost his job; he is flexing his 
muscles, he is showing that he can hit anyone. It is obvious 
that they can hit us. We are only 4.5 million people, so they 
can hit us very easily. But it will be a moral disaster for the 
NATO countries. You will see, in the event there are air 
strikes, many NATO countries will distance themselves 
immediately from this immoral move. 

</TEXT>

