<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Proximity Talks Begin; Kliridhis Meets UN Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1702112394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1000 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1702112394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The proximity talks on the confidence-building 
measures began this morning with a meeting between President 
Glavkos Kliridhis and UN officials. The UN officials were led 
by Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special representative 
on Cyprus. Participating in the UN team were Gustave Feissel, 
the UN secretary general's deputy special representative on 
Cyprus, and UNFICYP [UN Forces in Cyprus] political adviser John 
Paul Cavanagh. Also attending the talks were Foreign Minister 
Alekos Mikhailidhis, government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis, 
Deputy Minister to the President Pandelis Kouros, and Attorney 
General Mikhalakis Triandafillidhis. 
  Clark met with President Kliridhis for two and a half hours. 
Speaking after the meeting, Clark said that President Kliridhis 
and the UN officials dealt with all the issues on the agenda. 
He added that the seven key points and the maps were discussed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-39524 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu033_o_94003" </HT>


