<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Unanimously Accepts Measures Against Macedonia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1602194194 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1600 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1602194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said the 
Council of Ministers unanimously accepted the prime minister's 
proposal for measures against Skopje, and that the vast majority 
of the Greek people agree with this decision. He said: The 
Greek consulate in Skopje has already suspended its operations. 
UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali will be briefed today 
with a letter from Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias. 
  The spokesman stressed that the next Council of Ministers 
