<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Federation of Italian Socialists: </F>
Piro Becomes Secretary, Boniver Chairman"] 
  [Text] The Federation of Italian Socialists has elected 
Franco Piro as secretary and Margherita Boniver chairwoman. 
Both have launched "a cordial appeal to all registered 
socialists and sympathizers to unite their forces in view of the 
upcoming elections." In their opinion, "the tragic possibility 
exists that no socialist on the socialist lists will be elected 
to parliament. This happened previously only during the fascist 
era." They added: "We have made errors. However, no 
humiliation inflicted by the tabloid press can wipe out the 
results of history." 

