<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Orders Two Military Satellites </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1702141594 London HERMES Database in English 16 Feb 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1702141594 </F>
<F P=104>  London HERMES Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Press release issued by the UK Ministry of Defence: </F>
"Ministry of Defence Awards 300 Million Pounds Contract for 
Satellite Replacement"] 
  [Text] A contract worth over 300 million pounds has been 
awarded for two operational military communication satellites, 
Minister for Defence Procurement Jonathan Aitken announced 
today. Answering a Parliamentary Question from Rod Richards MP 
(Clwyd North West), Mr Aitken said: 
  "A contract worth some 300 million pounds has been awarded 
today for the development, production and delivery in orbit of 
two Skynet 4 Stage 2 military communication satellites. These 
will replace the existing Skynet 4 Stage 1 satellites as they 
approach the end of their operational life. 
  "British Aerospace is the prime contractor for this work. 
The 
main sub-contractors are Matra Marconi Space (UK) for satellite 
communications payload work and McDonnell Douglas and 
Arianespace for the launch vehicles. This is an important 
contract which will ensure the continued well-being of the UK's 
space industry and contribute to its long term future." 
<H5>  Notes To Editors: </H5>
  Skynet 4 Stage 2 will be accepted into service in March and 
December 1998. The satellites will be for the sole use of the UK 
military forces and are expected to be positioned in 
geostationary orbit at 1 degree west for the first satellite and 
either 53 degrees east or 34 degrees west for the second. 

</TEXT>

