<H3> <TI>   Rau, 'Arafat Hold `Surprise' Meeting 18 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1802124694 Hamburg DPA in German 1204 GMT 18 Feb 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1802124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Hague (DPA) -- North Rhine-Westphalian Minister 
President Johannes Rau held a surprise meeting with Palestinian 
leader Yasir 'Arafat in The Hague on Friday [18 February]. As 
Rau told the press, his meeting with the PLO head was arranged 
at short notice. Rau added that the Middle East peace process 
was the most important issue. 
  Rau said that they also discussed how Germany, and North 
Rhine-Westphalia, in particular, could help the Palestinians 
establish and extend administrative structures in the Gaza 
Strip, on the West Bank, and in Jericho. 

</TEXT>

