<H3> <TI>   Philippines Reportedly To Purchase Military Aircraft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1702150394 Antwerp GAZET VAN ANTWERPEN in Dutch 16 Feb 94 
p 21 </F>

<F P=103> BR1702150394 </F>
<F P=104>  Antwerp GAZET VAN ANTWERPEN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dutch </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Philippines Interested in 20 Belgian </F>
Mirage-5's"] 
  [Text] The Philippines are very interested in purchasing 20 
Belgian Mirage-5 fighter aircraft, according to BRTN 
[Dutch-speaking Belgian Television and Radio Broadcasting]. The 
negotiations are said to be in a relatively advanced stage, but 
for the time being nothing is known about the price to be paid 
by the Philippine Army. 
  When the Belgian Government agreed its medium-term 
purchasing 
plan for the Defense Ministry in the middle of last year, it 
immediately gave the green light for the sale of 20 Mirage-5 
aircraft. Sabca [Belgian Aeronautic Construction Company] was 
instructed to seek buyers. The aircraft had just been refitted 
when the government decided to slim down the Air Force. 
  At present they are deployed at the Weelde airbase. Before 
long the base will also station a number of F-16's which are 
also for sale. A number of countries have been contacted for 
this sale including Pakistan and NATO ally Greece. For the time 
being there has been no result here either. 

</TEXT>

