<F P=100> PORTUGAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israel, Portugal Abolish Visa Requirement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1702135594 Lisbon RTP Internacional Television in 
Portuguese 1200 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1702135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RTP Internacional Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Portugal and Israel today abolished the need for 
visas between the two countries. Good relations between 
Portugal and Israel were marked today by the ratification by the 
foreign minister of an accord abolishing the need for visas. 
The minister, Durao Barroso, who is visiting Israel, said that 
in addition to cultural, economic and tourist relations, human 
relations are now also facilitated by this bilateral accord on 
the abolition of visas. 

</TEXT>

