<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mikhailidhis Urges Denktas To Use `Goodwill' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1602222394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 2000 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1602222394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis said the Greek 
Cypriot side will attend tomorrow's proximity talks with clear 
positions, goodwill, and honesty. 
  Speaking this afternoon in Nicosia, Mikhailidhis added that 
if the other side shows the same goodwill we can move forward 
and reach an agreement on the confidence-building measures, 
which would be the beginning of a solution to the Cyprus 
problem. Mikhailidhis called on Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf 
Denktas to abandon his demands for separate sovereign rights. 
He added that European Union observer Serge Abou is expected in 
Cyprus next Monday [21 February]. 

</TEXT>

