<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Reportedly Changes Approach to Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1802093894 Nicosia O AGON in Greek 18 Feb 94 p 32 </F>
<F P=103> NC1802093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia O AGON </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Kostakis Andoniou] </F>
  [Text] "It is time to stop playing the dangerous game of 
`all or nothing' and see if we can make some progress with the 
Cyprus issue movement toward its final solution." 
  This is the philosophy with which President Glavkos 
Kliridhis 
approaches the discussion of the confidence-building measures, 
which he has explained to various political officials. 
  The president estimates that international circles are 
determined to press for the implementation of the 
confidence-building measures, considering them the beginning of 
the solution of the Cyprus issue. 
  In the meantime, political circles make the following 
assessment: If there is no agreement on the "most important" 
issues and aspects of the problem this time, the Cyprus issue 
will remain unsettled in the long run and there will be gradual 
legalization of the current situation through the recognition of 
the pseudostate. 
  The same political circles stressed that in a period when 
the 
international community has recognized almost 20 new states and 
ministates, it will not be particularly sensitive about 
recognizing one more. 

</TEXT>

