<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Overwhelming Support' for Embargo on Macedonia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1802170994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1230 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1802170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Greek Government's decision to impose an 
economic embargo against Skopje has caused diplomatic tension 
and marathon international deliberations. At the same time, 
Athens warns that it will impose stricter measures if Skopje 
does not stop its intransigence. Athens is also preparing to 
counter the charges from the European partners and Washington at 
the political and diplomatic level. 
  At the same time, the Greek immigrant community in Canada 
has 
expressed its enthusiasm for the actions and has sent 
congratulatory letters to Greek Prime Minister Andreas 
Papandreou. The overwhelming majority of voters in Greece agree 
with the measures imposed. According to an opinion poll 
conducted by private research companies in Attiki following the 
prime minister's announcement, 67 percent of those asked agreed 
with the measures. Consequently, according to political 
commentaries, there is overwhelming support for the government 
actions. 

</TEXT>

