<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry: Greek Decision on Macedonia `Unjust' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1702163394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1615 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1702163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 17 (A.A) -- Turkey on Thursday [17 
February] expressed concern over Greek decision taken toward 
Macedonia to impose sanctions on this country. 
  Foreign Ministry officials said "Turkey believed that Greek 
decision taken toward Macedonian Republic was unjust." 
  Officials said the decision was taken when the Balkans 
needed 
peace, stability, and cooperation. 
  It went on saying that the decision recalled "Cold War" 
period. 
  Greece said on Wednesday it was stopping The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia from using the Greek port of Thessaloniki 
for its supplies, except for humanitarian aid. 

</TEXT>

