Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb 17 (A.A) -- Iranian Embassy in Ankara 
denied on Thursday [17 February] that one of the outlawed 
separatist terrorist PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] 
organization leaders, Osman Ocalan, was in Iran. 
  Several Turkish newspapers earlier said Osman Ocalan was in 
Iran and Turkey and Iran was bargaining on his return. 
  The embassy in a written statement said several secret 
forces 
aimed at spoiling the two countries' relations. 

