Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Families of the diplomatic corps serving at the 
Turkish Embassy in Belgrade have left Serbia, two days before 
the NATO ultimatum expires. The group of 27 -- 17 children and 
10 women -- left Belgrade and entered Turkey from the Kapikule 
border post. 
  Other NATO member countries have already evacuated the 
families of their diplomatic corps. NATO countries with 
embassies in Belgrade have reportedly reduced the number of 
their diplomats. 

