<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Considers Redeploying Forces to Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1702174394 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1400 GMT 17 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1702174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Spanish Defense Minister Julian Garcia Vargas 
admitted today that he is considering the possibility of 
redeploying to Sarajevo the 130 Spanish blue helmets who are in 
the Bosnian city of Jablanica in response to the request for 
reinforcements made by the head of UN forces in Bosnia. 
  The minister, who spoke to the press after the swearing-in 
of 
the new Army chief of staff, said that for the present, until 
more precise details of the request are known, the Spanish blue 
helmets will remain in the area assigned to them at present -- 
Herzegovina, which is quite a long way from Sarajevo. 
  After admitting the possibility of redeploying the Spanish 
soldiers from Jablanica to Sarajevo, he explained that his first 
concern is the future of the area where the Spanish blue helmets 
are at present, above all the city of Mostar, which is their 
responsibility. 

</TEXT>

