Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus 
Kinkel has stressed that German soldiers' missions on AWACS 
flights will not be affected by possible NATO air strikes on 
Serbian positions. Bundeswehr soldiers staying on board NATO 
ships in the Adriatic are also covered by the Basic Law, Kinkel 
told the private television station Vox today. 
  The former Bundeswehr general Elmar Schmaehling warned 
earlier today that the participation of German soldiers on AWACS 
reconnaissance flights during a NATO air strike against Serbian 
positions in Bosnia would contravene the Basic Law. [passage 
omitted] 

