<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl: Sarajevo Offers `New Chance' for Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2102130794 Hamburg DPA in German 1231 GMT 21 Feb 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2102130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg (DPA) -- For Chancellor Helmut Kohl, the 
Serbs' withdrawal from the circle around Sarajevo is a "new 
chance" for peace in the former Yugoslavia. It is now possible 
"that the terrible murders will come to an end. First in this 
place and then in the others," Kohl said at the Hamburg 
Christian Democratic Union [CDU] Congress on Monday [21 
February]. 
  In the next few weeks, all one's power must be used to 
achieve an overall plan. Kohl advocated an international 
conference with "high-ranking" participants. 
  The Germans must not hide in a corner "when storms are 
blowing. Nobody will buy that," Kohl said. Such an attitude is 
a "shame for our country." 

</TEXT>

