<F P=101> Italy </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ciampi Views Solutions for Recession, Unemployment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1802144894 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1224 GMT 18 
Feb 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1802144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Ciampi on Recession and </F>
Unemployment, Solutions"] 
  [Text] Rome, 18 Feb (ANSA) -- Italy is still in the middle 
of a recession that has had serious effects on employment, Prime 
Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi conceded at a conference here 
Friday [18 February]. 
  The solutions, Ciampi suggested, lie in "consistent" 
attitudes at the next round of contract renewal talks and by the 
next government, which must pick up where this executive leaves 
off. 
  According to Ciampi, unemployment is caused by both external 
and structural conditions. Tackling both involves focusing on 
macro-economics, such as future labor accords in which wage 
increases are linked to production and private industry is 
encouraged to invest in infrastructures. 
  In the medium- and long-term, Ciampi continued, economic 
policies must follow the lines adopted by the European 
Commission in its job-creation plan, especially concerning 
investments. 
  In Italy in particular, he added, the government must pursue 
privatizations and the streamlining of public administration, 
increasing efficiency. At the same time, the job market must be 
made more "flexible" while maintaining protection for workers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

