<H3> <TI>   Asylum Applications Increase 38 Percent </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1302165894 Zurich NEUE ZUERCHER ZEITUNG in German 12 Feb 
94 p 27-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1302165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zurich NEUE ZUERCHER ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["U.M."-initialed report: "New Increase in Number of Asylum </F>
Applications by 38 Percent"] 
  [Excerpt] There were 24,739 asylum applications in 1993, a 
38 percent increase over the previous year and similar to the 
1989 level. More than 25 percent of the applicants came from 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina conflict area. At the end of 1993, a 
total of 118,321 asylum-seekers or refugees were staying in 
Switzerland. [passage omitted] 

