<H3> <TI>   Delcroix Denies Claes Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102150594 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International in 
English 1400 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgium's Defence Minister Leo Delcroix has denied 
that our country is sending troops to Sarajevo. Earlier today 
Foreign Affairs Minister Willy Claes said that Belgian soldiers 
would be transferred from Croatia to the Bosnian capital. But 
Mr. Delcroix has denied this, explaining that Mr. Claes, who is 
currently travelling through Africa, was wrongly informed. 

