<F P=100> BENELUX </F>
<F P=101> Netherlands </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Warns of Kosovo `Volcano' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102120594 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1130 GMT 
21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Netherlands Foreign Minister Peter Kooijmans wants 
the problems in the Serbian province of Kosovo to get more 
attention from the international mediators for ex-Yugoslavia. 
At a congress Mr. Kooijmans called Kosovo a volcano that could 
erupt at any moment. According to the foreign minister, an 
explosion of violence there must be prevented through dialogue. 
  Mr. Kooijmans places responsibility for the tense situation 
in the province primarily on the Serbs. Three years ago 
Belgrade ended the autonomous status of Kosovo, which has a 
majority population of ethnic Albanians. 

</TEXT>

