<H3> <TI>   Government Welcomes `Positive' Bosnia Signals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1802135194 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1347 GMT 
18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1802135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] "Positive signals are emerging": These optimistic 
comments were made by Prime Minister Ciampi about developments 
in Bosnia, following the Russian initiative (which Yeltsin had 
informed him about in advance). 
  Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri has also expressed optimism: 
"These are encouraging developments. Moscow has played a 
positive role in the peace process." But we must "wait for 
things to become certain before deactivating the NATO 
intervention plan." In other words NATO aircraft will remain on 
the runway at Aviano. 

</TEXT>

